## AI Development Governance

This project is equipped with comprehensive AI development workflow governance, generated by [bbg](https://github.com/nicepkg/bbg). When you open this project with any supported AI coding tool, you get a consistent, high-quality development workflow.

### Supported AI Tools

| Tool | Config Directory | Description |
|------|-----------------|-------------|
| Claude Code | `.claude/` | Settings, project skills, slash commands |
| OpenCode | `.opencode/` | Instructions, project skill adapters, commands |
| Cursor | `.cursor/rules/` | Project skill routing rules (.mdc) |
| Codex CLI | `.codex/` | Config, AGENTS.md, project-local bridge skills |
| Gemini | `.gemini/` | Settings, project skill adapters, reusable prompts |

### Model Selection

bbg does not pin a required model for any AI tool. It manages workflow entrypoints, runtime context, review gates, and role/capability guidance.

Choose any supported model in your current tool that matches the work:

- planner work: strong reasoning and architecture analysis
- implementer work: strong code editing and iterative verification
- reviewer work: strong code review and risk detection

If your tool supports switching models directly, keep using the tool and change the model there instead of changing bbg-generated files.

