## Getting Started

1. Open this project with your AI coding tool of choice
2. The tool will automatically load its configuration from the appropriate directory
3. Ask the AI to use `.bbg/harness/skills/analyze/SKILL.md` the first time you work in this project or after major repository changes
4. Ask the AI to use `.bbg/harness/skills/add-repo/SKILL.md` when adding another repository into the workspace
5. Ask the AI to use `.bbg/harness/skills/start/SKILL.md` to begin implementation work
6. Ask the AI to use `.bbg/harness/skills/resume/SKILL.md` or run `bbg status` when switching tools or continuing later
7. Ask the AI to use `.bbg/harness/skills/deliver/SKILL.md` when you need a customer-facing delivery report
8. Reference agents in `.bbg/harness/agents/` and skills in `.bbg/harness/skills/` for specialized guidance

### Task Resume Guidance

When resuming a task, prefer the structured task state files over ad-hoc memory:

1. `.bbg/tasks/<task-id>/context.json`
2. `.bbg/tasks/<task-id>/handoff.md`
3. `.bbg/tasks/<task-id>/decisions.json`

If your AI tool was launched by `bbg`, it may also receive structured runtime hints through:

- `BBG_TASK_ID`
- `BBG_TASK_STATUS`
- `BBG_TASK_STEP`
- `BBG_HANDOFF_PATH`
- `BBG_CONTEXT_PATH`
- `BBG_DECISIONS_PATH`
- `BBG_RESUME_STRATEGY`
- `BBG_RECOVERY_PLAN`
- `BBG_RECOVERY_ACTIONS`
- `BBG_ATTEMPT_COUNT`
- `BBG_VERIFY_FAILURE_COUNT`
- `BBG_AUTONOMY_ESCALATED`
- `BBG_AUTONOMY_ESCALATION_REASON`

